US correspondent, Simon Marks, gives more details on this story. Courtesy #DStv403 NEW YORK - The Omicron Covid-19 variant is wreaking havoc in the US. Data from Johns Hopkins University reveals the country recorded over a million infections on Monday. A new record for that country making it the hardest hit by the pandemic. Despite the record numbers, many Americans are still reluctant to get Covid-19 vaccine booster shots. Many children and teenagers are also falling severely ill.